# [App Name] — Design Research

> Output of Phase 1 (Research) in `pipeline/build/ORCHESTRATOR_BRIEF.md`.
> Ground-truth reference for the clone. Every claim here must trace to a
> saved screenshot under `spec/screenshots/`. Copy this file to
> `spec/RESEARCH.md` and fill it in. Do NOT ship RESEARCH.md with any
> `TODO` or `[fill]` placeholders — Phase 2 will not enter until this file
> passes the Phase 1 exit gate in ORCHESTRATOR_BRIEF.md.

## Document contract (read before editing)

This file is one of four that must stay in sync. If you change one, update
the others in the same commit.

- `pipeline/build/ORCHESTRATOR_BRIEF.md` — the pipeline. Owns: phases,
  exit conditions, gates, subagent split. Reads: `FEATURES.md`, this file,
  `TASK_PLAN.md`.
- `spec/FEATURES.md` — the scope. Owns: feature inventory, Tier 1 vs Tier 2,
  failure-mode targets, seed data totals. Reads: this file (tokens),
  `TASK_PLAN.md` (task-driven seed).
- `spec/RESEARCH.md` (this file) — the UI spec. Owns: screenshots,
  design tokens, per-page layout, interactive state matrix, required
  data-testids. Reads: `spec/FEATURES.md` (which pages exist at all).
- `spec/TASK_PLAN.md` — the task spec. Owns: failure-mode selection,
  per-task end-state, difficulty, seed-determinism mapping.

Phase → file map:
- Phase 1 writes: this file and `spec/FEATURES.md`.
- Phase 2 writes: `spec/TASK_PLAN.md` and the System Plan. Reads all four.
- Phase 3 subagents read: all four docs; never re-derive tokens, pages,
  tiers, interactive states, or task design.
- Phase 4 reads: § "Interactive state matrix" below as the UI fidelity bar.

