## 4. Interactive state matrix (the fidelity bar)

This is the most important section. Phase 4 walks this table row by row.
Every target element must have rows for `default`, `hover`, `focus`,
`active`. Inputs, dropdowns, and any button that can be disabled must
also have a `disabled` row. Every row must cite a screenshot filename.

Target elements (extend with app-specific ones you encounter):

- Primary pill buttons (Share, Upgrade, Done, Save)
- Secondary / outline buttons (Copy link, Cancel)
- Icon buttons in toolbars (undo, redo, bold, italic, underline, ...)
- Menu-bar items (File / Edit / View / Insert / Format / Tools / Help / ...)
- Menu items inside dropdowns (including submenu parents with `▸`)
- Combobox / select controls (font, font-size, style, zoom)
- Mode dropdowns (Editing / Suggesting / Viewing, density, sort order)
- Cards and rows in list/grid views (hover, selected, focused)
- 3-dot "more" buttons on cards and rows
- Tabs / pills (left panel tabs, gallery tabs)
- Text inputs and searchboxes (default, focus, filled, disabled, error)
- Star / favorite / checkbox toggles (off, on, hover, focus)
- Role dropdowns inside share modals
- General-access dropdowns inside share modals
- Right-click context menus on cards and rows
- Ruler / drag handles (default, drag-in-progress, snapped)
- Avatar / account button

